   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1872_07_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Pandel_Stiehaus_Nachfolger_Batavia_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>PANDEL &amp; STIEHAUS Successors<lb/>BATAVIA<lb/>JAVA Batavia, 3rd July
                1872<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler + Co Yokohama<lb/>(Japan)<lb/>Having been without
                esteemed news from you for <lb/>some time, we are today taking the liberty of
                supplying <lb/>you with the enclosed small bill of exchange <lb/>⟨M440⟩ over $ 17.50
                on the agents of the P &amp; O Co there<lb/>which we ask you kindly to
                endorse;<lb/>after receipt we will be pleased to receive <lb/>the net provenues[?],
                having deducted your <lb/>costs, in a bill of exchange in Singapore,<lb/>and we give
                you our warmest thanks in advance<lb/>for the effort this is going to cause you.
                <lb/>In our market it is calmer with regard to imports <lb/>than we are used to at
                this time of year. <lb/>Stocks of staple goods are, though not <lb/>excessive,
                rather ample and therefore <lb/> it is difficult to increase the proceeds <lb/>for
                these. <lb/>We sold in recent days <lb/>
         </p>
         <table rend="rules">
            <row>
               <cell>
                        [...]
                    </cell>
               <cell>grey shirtings at </cell>
               <cell>fl 6 ¾ %[?]</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
               <cell>d<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>¼[?]</cell>
               <cell>＂ ＂ </cell>
               <cell>7 ¾ ＂</cell>
            </row>
         </table>
         <p>
            <lb/>and despite the high prices for these articles <lb/>in Europe there is for the
                time being no prospect<lb/>of achieving more. <lb/>[...] Turkish[?] alone is getting
                    <del rend="overstrike">after</del> some<lb/> attention, but offers for it do not
                exceed <lb/> fl 390.- ⅌ bale, both the producers and the <lb/>wholesalers are still
                well stocked with this <lb/>article, and therefore a rise in the prices is</p>
         <pb facs="1872_07_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Pandel_Stiehaus_Nachfolger_Batavia_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>not to be expected yet any time soon. <lb/>In terms of woolen wares, black &amp;
                blue<lb/>minon cloth of a good quality remains in lively demand<lb/>and can be sold,
                depending on quality, for fl 1.50.- 1.99 <lb/>per cubit. Marsurdt imitation
                lastings<lb/>are also in higher demand again. <lb/>Rice. The harvest this year has
                overall <lb/>not been very good, which is a result of the <lb/>floods that happened
                in spring, and<lb/>there cannot be any doubt that the prices <lb/>for this are going
                to rise.<lb/>
            <table>
               <row>
                  <cell> 1a[?] Batavia rice fetches</cell>
                  <cell> fl 200 - 210._ p Kogang</cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell>2<hi rend="superscript">a</hi> ＂</cell>
                  <cell>180-195 ＂ </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <lb/>Rates are subdued 6 month d[?]Holland Bank 103½%[?] 6 ＂ S England ＂
                11.50<lb/>We send your our cordial greetings, <lb/>Yours
                respectfully<lb/>Pandel+Stiehaus<lb/>Successors</p>
         <pb facs="1872_07_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Pandel_Stiehaus_Nachfolger_Batavia_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1872_07_03_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Pandel_Stiehaus_Nachfolger_Batavia_4.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>per steamer<lb/>POSS NEER<lb/>4<lb/>JUIL.<lb/>72<lb/>[?]<lb/>Messrs
                BATAVIA<lb/>3<lb/>7<lb/>18[?]72<lb/>L. Kniffler+ Co.<lb/>PANDEL &amp;
                STIEHAUS<lb/>BATAVIA.<lb/>SUCCESSORS Yokohama<lb/>Japan<lb/>
                YOKOHAMA<lb/>24<lb/>JUIL.[?]<lb/>72<lb/>BAU FRANCAIS<lb/>⟨1872<lb/>Batavia 3rd
                July<lb/>Pandel + Stiehaus Successors<lb/>R[eceived] 24th et.<lb/>Aug 6th ⟩</p>
      </body>
